In these cases you must retain this copyright notice and license in source
copies you distribute.

## 2. Commercial use (paid services)

If you use this software as part of a **paid** product or service (including
but not limited to: commercial SaaS, subscriptions, paid access, marketplaces,
or any model where users pay to use the service), you must satisfy **one** of
the following:

### Option A — Visible attribution

Display the following **clearly, permanently, and visibly** to end users:

> Powered by [Cocina Server](https://github.com/montvlein/cocina-chat-local-server) by
> Fabricio Montivero

Attribution must appear at least in:
- The main product interface (e.g. footer or About screen), and
- Public documentation or the service landing page.

### Option B — Commercial license

Contact the copyright holder and obtain a **paid commercial license** in writing.
With a valid commercial license, public attribution under Option A is not
required.

Commercial licensing contact: montvlein@gmail.com

